    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nUI events and editor events are needlessly separated. For example, `VimLeave` already exists, but to \"listen\" for that even, the UI client has to set up a handler that then sends a custom event. Or we have to create a new `exit` UI event that basically just duplicates `VimLeave`. https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/34365#issuecomment-2955820485\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nAllow `nvim_ui_attach()` to opt-in to receiving editor events on the channel as msgpack-rpc notifications. The events will include the fulls serialized state of `v:event` and any `:help event-args`.",
